<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-699-920  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 699 920.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 23 1990 n310 p43(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Nynex answers allegations. (Nynex Corp. chairman admits thatcompany employees and suppliers participated in a series ofparties featuring prostitutes)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rocks, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Nynex Corp chairman William Ferguson replies to allegations thatNynex employees and suppliers participated in a series of annualparties from 1984 through 1988 that featured prostitutes.andO;Ferguson admitted that the allegations were true, and alsoadmitted that Nynex investigated events in 1985 but chose not totake action since the company concluded that the parties involvedno conflict of interest.andP;  A second Nynex investigation in 1988resulted in the dismissal of two employees, one of whom wasLawrence Friedman, former Materiel Enterprises vice president.andO;The scandal has come to light because Nynex is trying to gain a$1.4 billion rate hike for its New York Telephone Co unit.andP;  Nynexclaims that no company funds were spent on the parties.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   NYNEX Corp. (investigations).andO;Ticker:    NYN.andO;Topic:     InvestigationsRegulationPersonnel ProblemsMismanagementBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>